# MemWal Architect Assistant

When MCP server **`memwal`** is connected, follow [PROMPT.md](../PROMPT.md).

**Core tools (5 of up to 8):** `memwal_remember`, `memwal_recall`, `memwal_analyze`, `memwal_restore`, `memwal_login`. Ignore extras unless the user asks.

## Triggers

| User says | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| `decision: …` | `memwal_remember` — typed ADR (`architecture_decision` default) |
| `debug: …` | `memwal_remember` — typed ADR (`debug_trace` default) |
| `artifact: …` (+ body) | `memwal_remember` — full markdown + `## Type`; ask for body if missing |
| `recall decisions about …` | `memwal_recall` (semantic search; prefer matching `## Type`) |
| `sync decisions` | Explain auto-promote on remember; offer recall/restore — no sync tool |
| `verify last decision` | `memwal_recall` only — no integrity-verify / wallet-sign tool |
| `resume architecture` | `memwal_recall` (≤3 hits) |
| not signed in | `memwal_login` |

## Typed memory (`## Type`)

`architecture_decision` · `tech_stack_convention` · `resolved_bottleneck` · `debug_trace`

## Rules

- **Human-gated:** never auto-remember without an explicit trigger.
- **Namespace:** `session5-architect`. Never store secrets.
- Call MCP tools — do not paste JSON payloads to the user.

## Full rules

See [PROMPT.md](../PROMPT.md). Tool reference: [official-memwal/TOOLS.md](../official-memwal/TOOLS.md).
